<normalizedToken id="18129DC320BE472C2E18CE13137078D8" originalValue="Xiá">Xia</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="F92F84F0D1E4955B2C8699B12764479A" originalValue="Tōng">Tōng</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="24FBA3D185478945AFF70C276B53697F" originalValue="Quán">Quan</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="A65FEB04603ECA2B1DBF1D4076813287" originalValue="Căo">Căo</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A10385CCF4433B3560FB7F49B8DB9CE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="provisional conservation status">
<paragraph id="9DC7393DFEF4DE191626A36B1E61C937" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Provisional conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="094901E97F21F7CAA31D909385D38589" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Based on our special botanical surveys for Danxia landforms in Jiangxi Province in 2021, 
<taxonomicName id="8077BD7407A4452A2E14B9F7900A35C0" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="9E93D5D9AC57E216C69B8D165CDCFFD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been discovered only from one single locality so far in Liukou Town of Guixi City in Jiangxi Province, China, and 2 populations were found in the locality, which totally occupied ca. 200 m2. In these populations, a total of ca. 80 fruiting individuals were counted in August 2021 and there were a lot of seedlings in each of the population when we firstly encountered the species in June 2021 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3B0C0E3EAF161A4B1D82F7DCE4688455" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Morphology of Mazus danxiacola sp. nov. A habitat B seedlings C habit D a flowering individual E fruiting specimens F roots G fruit H leaves I a mature inflorescence with flowers and fruits J young inflorescence, showing dense pubescence and glandular hairs K flower (lateral view) L palate, showing the conspicuously long and clavate gland-like hairs. Scale bars: 2 cm (B, H); 5 cm (C); 1 cm (F, I); 2 mm (G, J, K, L)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.85717.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691694" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">1B, C</figureCitation>
), indicating that the species has a well-developed reproductive strategy in the habitat of Danxia landform. However, the locality is close to downtown of Guixi City, has not been projected to a nature reserve yet and all populations are obviously facing man-made interferences, such as deforestation, touring and grazing, we thus propose to categorize the species as critically endangered (CR) under criteria B and D following IUCN Red List Categories (
<bibRefCitation id="D41484C17306E2CC543352FA6EB26E77" author="Hsieh, TH" journalOrPublisher="Taiwania" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B8" refString="IUCN (2022) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 15. Prepared by the Standards and petitions Committee." year="2000">IUCN 2022</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="83591148DE2C434851989610CC11F268" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="61A949B0A449FE1D2ABA7D375CF67120" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Taxonomic note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C4FEF97626830D054E64A7116EE5B122" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="67F265D121BE18D4C877701FDADEFAAF" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="6E0543B5EF68330C6C42C9EC7DF6A581" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears a series of rare traits which are not common in 
<taxonomicName id="39E6FB9A37301C59AC7FB36AE5C89D4B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Mazaceae" genus="Mazus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mazus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="766FAF04D05D363BA88E2E694435D921" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Mazus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as annual habit, single erect unbranched stems, without basal leaves, stem leaves many and alternate, extremely long petioles up to 4.5 cm, abaxial leaf surface grayish green to silver gray, and palate of corolla densely covered by conspicuously clavate gland-like hairs. The combination of these traits makes 
<taxonomicName id="59ECEE059812D246F0E4731E2FB56DC4" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="B6644F3B72C247316DE8E32EBCBDBE5A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinct from all other congeneric taxa. Our molecular phylogenetic analyses based on cpDNA dataset indicated that 
<taxonomicName id="7D08A1A558591FFF13ACB1DFBE4DCD63" genus="M." lsidName="M. fauriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="fauriei">
<emphasis id="8D091A8C637E5F003210F3E2AF548255" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. fauriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="34B84C5760B581568BFEE0B8C20F5FE2" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="A100E09D1151D9140FF059430928A8FF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2E8E1F487A7A52EE2B3A320460E7F168" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Maximum Likelihood phylogram of Mazus as inferred from analysis of combined dataset of matK, rbcL, rps 16 and trnL - trnF. Support values ≥ 50 % BS or 0.90 PP are displayed above and below the branches, respectively." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.85717.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691695" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">2</figureCitation>
), but 
<taxonomicName id="6F95373FCF06FA1D1BFC256CDF4DF5E5" genus="M." lsidName="M. fauriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="fauriei">
<emphasis id="83D39B09B96400A25CC177FE42F45C75" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. fauriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a perennial herb with all leaves basal and rosulate and petioles broadly winged (
<bibRefCitation id="1D920F13EB6778E380C289617D83F402" author="Hong, DY" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="18. Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 212" refId="B6" refString="Hong, DY, Yang, HB, Jin, CL, Holmgren, NH, 1998. Scrophulariaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., Flora of China, Vol. 18. Science Press, Beijing: 1 - 212" title="Scrophulariaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China, Vol." year="1998">Hong et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
), which is apparently different from 
<taxonomicName id="8D6525DD91179AECA0277ECF867A64C6" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="C490927E08CF02484C2C3686D58F8B45" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that has only cauline leaves and long unwinged petioles. In the nrITS trees, 
<taxonomicName id="47ACD9493D40143325AAA50CF0157D46" genus="M." lsidName="M. pumilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="pumilis">
<emphasis id="4C4825EE7CDED309EBAAE4BDD9F0B68A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. pumilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D2979CC957A81A2BF3A8191C3906CA1C" genus="M." lsidName="M. gracilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="77A948558C196A5544209D27037E7E8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were shown as possible alliances of 
<taxonomicName id="21560EEEA1FD00104195FD8E34F653CE" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="0394CE1CB51048C7077C589750C42740" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, cauline leaves of the former two species are always opposite, and their basal and cauline leaves are all decurrent to form short petioles (
<bibRefCitation id="A4964386474A441FBD4A06F105B96A4A" author="Hong, DY" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="18. Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 212" refId="B6" refString="Hong, DY, Yang, HB, Jin, CL, Holmgren, NH, 1998. Scrophulariaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., Flora of China, Vol. 18. Science Press, Beijing: 1 - 212" title="Scrophulariaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China, Vol." year="1998">Hong et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
), clearly differing from those alternate and long petiolate leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="2C608AEE768542649F8EED6B8A9C87F1" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="407AD7D6A3BDFE521320D47B54F750AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is worth mentioning that there are obvious conflicts between the cpDNA and nrITS phylogenies which have been discovered and discussed in a previous study (
<bibRefCitation id="03F4589CC9C29C508BCE741FF5B328B0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.171.61926" author="Xiang, CL" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 24" refId="B19" refString="Xiang, CL, Pan, HL, Min, DZ, Zhang, DG, Zhao, F, Liu, B, Li, B, 2021. Rediscovery of Mazus lanceifolius reveals a new genus and a new species in Mazaceae. PhytoKeys 171: 1 - 24, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.171.61926" title="Rediscovery of Mazus lanceifolius reveals a new genus and a new species in Mazaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.171.61926" volume="171" year="2021">Xiang et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). In fact, the available molecular data of 
<taxonomicName id="CF9007D123DCAF174D2FF375391E259D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Mazaceae" genus="Mazus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mazus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D2B8FDBB2A878C517FEAF866F3FBCA6D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Mazus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not sufficient enough to represent all known species of the genus, thus it is hard to definitely confirm the closest relatives of 
<taxonomicName id="C7EA4A8EDB78D7807D83831C1BDD2B72" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="3A09FBCF12CB231C1794AC620A931264" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the moment through molecular phylogenetics. Future molecular studies including more species at population level and using more DNA markers may shed light on the determination of specific relationships within 
<taxonomicName id="C4E5A4D6CCD78C6D04E12BC04C6B2C9F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Mazaceae" genus="Mazus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mazus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E350A6DAC9059942E8721D72A5EBC8C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Mazus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7B29C1F714E2A77281AD07D42412EEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
So far, 
<taxonomicName id="78ECA219F6C2C7627C1FF4E566B9C584" genus="M." lsidName="M. danxiacola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="danxiacola">
<emphasis id="EFACCC83C896C782490BBF50DE22DA16" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. danxiacola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the first species of 
<taxonomicName id="D0CBA9AC80C81C8083C4BE50002725C9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Mazaceae" genus="Mazus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mazus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0042A051D328C69744419A638FE00FDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Mazus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was found to be endemic to Danxia landform. Danxia landform is a unique type of petrographic geomorphology found in southeast, southwest, and northwest China with a high level of floral endemism (
<bibRefCitation id="DC10EE30C8F8E8D6F82B70DB5507519B" author="Liu, WQ" journalOrPublisher="Guangxi Zhi Wu" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="15 - 21" refId="B10" refString="Liu, WQ, Li, ZH, Liu, LF, 1999. A preliminary study on the flora of the tourist landform of Danxiashan, Guangdong, China. Guangxi Zhi Wu 19: 15 - 21" title="A preliminary study on the flora of the tourist landform of Danxiashan, Guangdong, China." volume="19" year="1999">Liu et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="AE78EB06707195F821CD310B7D326FB3" author="Liu, SR" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Mountain Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="669 - 674" refId="B9" refString="Liu, SR, Liu, RH, 2003. On the conception of Danxia Landforms. Journal of Mountain Science 21: 669 - 674" title="On the conception of Danxia Landforms." volume="21" year="2003">Liu and Liu 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6315255C69AD84B7AC9C8ECC7CD4304A" author="Luo, WW" journalOrPublisher="Zhiwu Ziyuan Yu Huanjing" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="84 - 91" refId="B11" refString="Luo, WW, Yuan, SB, Liu, SC, Zhong, ZL, Kuang, JJ, Luo, ZC, 2010. Analysis and comparison of flora characteristics of vascular plants in &quot;Danxia&quot; geomorphological area of Langshan Mountain in Hunan. Zhiwu Ziyuan Yu Huanjing 19: 84 - 91" title="Analysis and comparison of flora characteristics of vascular plants in &quot; Danxia &quot; geomorphological area of Langshan Mountain in Hunan." volume="19" year="2010">Luo et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). In southeast China, Danxia landforms are well developed in Guangdong, Fujian, Jiangxi, and Hunan provinces, and the special environment, including deep valleys, grooves, moist caves, cliffy rocks, dry cliff-tops and shaded rock bottoms (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="418895EBDBCB1D24F40796487E4894D9" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Danxia landform of the type locality of Mazus danxiacola sp. nov. (left) and the habitat of the new species under a cliff (right). Arrows show where the population could be found." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.85717.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691698" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">5</figureCitation>
), has significant effects on the growth of special plants (
<bibRefCitation id="39262614486C2D3D93E5C91C35548F60" author="Chen, BM" journalOrPublisher="Ecology &amp; Environment" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1058 - 1062" refId="B1" refString="Chen, BM, Li, J, Peng, SL, Fu, YF, Pang, JX, Hou, RF, Peng, H, 2008. Preliminary study on diversity of vegetation community and ecosystem of Danxia landform in South China. Ecology &amp; Environment 17: 1058 - 1062" title="Preliminary study on diversity of vegetation community and ecosystem of Danxia landform in South China." volume="17" year="2008">Chen et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Just in the last ten years, a lot of new taxa have been continuously discovered from Danxia mountains of these provinces, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="815AF328DC39F3D122982EFCA7002F3C" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Danxiaorchis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Danxiaorchis" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7EC000DDBBE3B9B37DB1A3349B95520" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Danxiaorchis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J.W. Zhai, F.W. Xing &amp; Z.J. Liu (
<bibRefCitation id="D5211B719CB83D12FCC88A1B078E48D3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0060371" author="Zhai, JW" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B23" refString="Zhai, JW, Zhang, GQ, Chen, LJ, Xiao, XJ, Liu, KW, Tsai, WC, Hsiao, YY, Tian, HZ, Zhu, JQ, Wang, MN, Wang, FG, Xing, FW, Liu, ZJ, 2013. A new orchid genus, Danxiaorchis, and phylogenetic analysis of the tribe Calypsoeae. PLoS ONE 8(4): e60371. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0060371" title="A new orchid genus, Danxiaorchis, and phylogenetic analysis of the tribe Calypsoeae. PLoS ONE 8 (4): e 60371." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0060371" year="2013">Zhai et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="6E6697EEB0FD176ECC9F952C437C4151" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis danxiashanensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danxiashanensis">
<emphasis id="6F7053EF7E7DECB591A34CE2D3D2248F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Spiradiclis danxiashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.J. Wang (
<bibRefCitation id="530133C277C8BF7CEB029CCE6ABF1725" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.206.1.5" author="Wang, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="30 - 36" refId="B18" refString="Wang, RJ, Wen, HZ, Deng, SJ, Zhou, LX, 2015. Spiradiclis danxiashanensis (Rubiaceae), a new species from south China. Phytotaxa 206 (1): 30 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.206.1.5" title="Spiradiclis danxiashanensis (Rubiaceae), a new species from south China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.206.1.5" volume="206" year="2015">Wang et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="A155D65A75A040AF89756201B8283A85" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Viola" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Viola hybanthoides" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybanthoides">
<emphasis id="3977B3209D20BF0B616EA2202312FFD4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Viola hybanthoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W.B. Liao &amp; Q. Fan (
<bibRefCitation id="BE7933758E2A6D00F173AEEC30EDDDD1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.197.1.2" author="Fan, Q" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="15 - 26" refId="B4" refString="Fan, Q, Chen, SF, Wang, LY, Chen, ZX, Liao, WB, 2015. A new species and new section of Viola (Violaceae) from Guangdong, China. Phytotaxa 197 (1): 15 - 26, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.197.1.2" title="A new species and new section of Viola (Violaceae) from Guangdong, China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.197.1.2" volume="197" year="2015">Fan et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="FBDB93E36D372CBE6872E6DAAE9730D0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia danxiaensis" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danxiaensis">
<emphasis id="CBA6A57D381032856F09B00F13563820" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Begonia danxiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D.K. Tian &amp; X.L. Yu (
<bibRefCitation id="BEBADFD93FDE3C3A4E56793FAE912183" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.407.1.12" author="Tian, DK" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="101 - 110" refId="B16" refString="Tian, DK, Li, C, Yu, XL, Zhou, JJ, Liu, KM, Shu, JP, Zhou, XL, Xiao, Y, 2019. A new tuberous species of Begonia sect. Diploclinium endemic to Danxia landforms in central China. Phytotaxa 407 (1): 101 - 110, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.407.1.12" title="A new tuberous species of Begonia sect. Diploclinium endemic to Danxia landforms in central China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.407.1.12" volume="407" year="2019">Tian et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="53117669D140A00C94B5034BD010E9C8" authorityName="N.H.Xia &amp; X.R.Zheng" authorityYear="2019" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phyllostachys" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Phyllostachys danxiashanensis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danxiashanensis">
<emphasis id="BC72C46A11DDB714E515A6BF37BD2D56" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Phyllostachys danxiashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
N.H. Xia &amp; X.R. Zheng (
<bibRefCitation id="0B16E87E05C71F364C3CF594DF8BEEB9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.388.2.7" author="Zheng, XR" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="201 - 206" refId="B25" refString="Zheng, XR, Tong, YH, Ni, JB, Chen, ZX, Xia, NH, 2019. Phyllostachys danxiashanensis (Poaceae: Bambusoideae), a new species from south China. Phytotaxa 388 (2): 201 - 206, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.388.2.7" title="Phyllostachys danxiashanensis (Poaceae: Bambusoideae), a new species from south China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.388.2.7" volume="388" year="2019">Zheng et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
